'''Laudica''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Homeworld/Legends|from]] the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] who worked as a [[Smuggler/Legends|gun-runner]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. She was known for her skills as a [[Sniper/Legends|markswoman]] and was one of many criminals who frequented [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|the palace]] of the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. Laudica was present in the palace in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] when the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] [[Siege of Jabba's Palace|arrived]] in order to bargain for the life of [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|their master's]] friend [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]. She witnessed several more of Solo's friends subsequently arrive until Jabba sentenced them to die in Tatooine's [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Great Pit of Carkoon]].

==Biography==
The [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|female]] Laudica [[Homeworld/Legends|hailed]] from<ref name="db" /> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="Corellia">{{DB|location|corellia|Corellia}}</ref> [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]].<ref name="db" /> During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], she was employed as a [[Smuggler/Legends|gun-runner]] and had developed a reputation for her skills as a [[Sniper/Legends|markswoman]].<ref name="ccg" /> Laudica was good friends with many other female criminals,<ref name="btm">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref> including<ref name="ccg" /> fellow [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] smuggler<ref name="Brindy DB">{{DB|character|brindytruchong|Truchong, Brindy}}</ref> [[Brindy Truchong]] and the<ref name="ccg" /> [[Kiffar/Legends|Kiffar]] [[Con artist/Legends|con artist]]<ref name="Tonnikas' DB">{{DB|character|tonnikasisters|Tonnika, Brea & Senni}}</ref> [[Tonnika sisters/Legends|Tonnika sisters]]. Despite her better judgment, she was romantically involved with [[Rayc Ryjerd]].<ref name="ccg" />

[[File:Laudica_ROTJ.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Laudica watches Princess Leia bargain with Jabba.]]
During the war, Laudica became a frequent visitor of [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|the palace]] of<ref name="db" /> the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]]<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|130|Jabba the Hutt (Jabba Desilijic Tiure)}}</ref> [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]]<ref name="db" /> on the planet<ref name="CL">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2005)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. She was in the palace in<ref name="rotj" /> [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]]<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates the events of {{Film|VI}} to [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> when [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], [[Droid/Legends|droids]] belonging to the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], [[Siege of Jabba's Palace|arrived]] in order to bargain for the life of [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], a friend of Skywalker's who was frozen in [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]] and who hung on the wall of the palace's courtroom. Shortly after the droids' arrival, Laudica watched as Jabba dropped his [[Slavery/Legends|slave]] dancer [[Oola/Legends|Oola]] into the pit of [[Jabba's rancor/Legends|his rancor]].<ref name="rotj" />

Laudica was in the courtroom shortly thereafter when Solo's friend [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], disguised as the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Boushh/Legends|Boushh]], arrived with the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] and threatened to destroy the palace with a [[Thermal detonator/Legends|thermal detonator]]. Organa stayed her hand and thus won Jabba's favor, but she later [[Rescue of Han Solo/Legends|freed]] Solo from carbonite and attempted to escape the palace with him. When Jabba caught and [[Prisoner/Legends|imprisoned]] them, Skywalker came to the palace to demand their release and was dropped into the [[Rancor/Legends|rancor]] pit himself. He [[Death/Legends|killed]] the rancor, however, prompting Jabba to sentence him, Solo, and Chewbacca to die in Tatooine's [[Great Pit of Carkoon/Legends|Great Pit of Carkoon]]. Laudica and many other members of Jabba's entourage followed Skywalker and Solo as they were dragged out of the courtroom.<ref name="rotj" />

==Personality and traits==
Laudica had many friends<ref name="btm" /> and followed her romantic desires rather than her better judgment by dating Rayc Ryjerd.<ref name="ccg" /> When Oola was dropped into Jabba's rancor pit, Laudica watched and jeered in delight as she was eaten by the creature. She had [[Color/Legends|light]] skin and black hair.<ref name="rotj" />

==Skills and abilities==
Laudica was a skilled markswoman.<ref name="ccg" />

==Equipment==
During her time in the Palace, Laudica wore a red [[Jumpsuit/Legends|jumpsuit]] with a white [[Belt/Legends|belt]].<ref name="rotj" /> She used a [[Blaster pistol/Legends|blaster pistol]].<ref name="db" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Mara fans that have painstakingly freeze-framed all the palace footage have found a number of hopeful contenders: the redheaded dancing girl that flirts with Boba Fett, for instance. That's Rystáll. There's also a woman with short dark hair, red jumpsuit, and white belt. That's Laudica. There's a scantily clad girl with platinum blonde hair, bare midriff, and flirtatious eye on Bib Fortuna. Her name is Jess.|Author [[Pablo Hidalgo]], explaining who in Jabba's Palace is not Mara Jade|<ref name="Not Mara">{{InsiderCite|66|Ask Lobot}}</ref>}}
[[File:ROTJ_polaroid_Laudica.jpg|thumb|200px|A photo from the set of ''Return of the Jedi'' including Laudica]]
Laudica first appeared in [[Richard Marquand]]'s [[1983]] film {{Film|VI}}, where she was portrayed by an uncredited extra.<ref name="rotj" /> The palace scenes, which featured Laudica, were filmed between [[January 25]] and [[February 8]], [[1982]] on Stage 8 at [[Elstree Studios]].<ref name="Making of">''[[The Making of Return of the Jedi]]''</ref> The ''[[Jabba's Palace Limited]]'' set of the [[Decipher]] [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]], released in [[1998]], included a card that gave the character that identified the character.<ref name="ccg" />

Some fans have confused Laudica, among other denizens of Jabba's courtroom, for [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]], an [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] character who was established to have been a dancer in the palace during Luke Skywalker's [[Time/Legends|time]] there.<ref name="Not Mara" /> In the [[1996]] short story ''[[Sleight of Hand: The Tale of Mara Jade]]''&mdash;written before the release of ''Jabba's Palace Limited''&mdash;author [[Timothy Zahn]] described a dance designer in Jabba's Palace named [[Melina Carniss]] as dark-haired, wearing a red jumpsuit, and crouching over the rancor pit after Oola was dropped in. However, despite her similarities to the then-unnamed Laudica,<ref name="Sleight of Hand">{{StoryCite|story=Sleight of Hand: The Tale of Mara Jade|book=Tales from Jabba's Palace}}</ref> ''Jabba's Palace Limited'' established that the two are different characters.<ref name="ccg" />

[[File:Laudica_and_Jess_-_Return_of_the_Ewok.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Laudica in ''Return of the Ewok'']]
Laudica additionally appears in ''[[Return of the Ewok]]'', a mockumentary created by actor [[Warwick Davis]] during his time on the set of ''Return of the Jedi'', that blends elements of the movie with the real world. In the short film, Davis, dressed as [[Wicket Wystri Warrick/Legends|Wicket]] the [[Ewok/Legends|Ewok]], wanders onto the set of Jabba's Palace while searching for the [[Forest/Legends|Forest]] [[Moon/Legends|Moon]] of [[Endor/Legends|Endor]]. He finds Laudica and the dancer [[Jess/Legends|Jess]] rehearsing a choreographed dance to [[Lapti Nek/Legends|Lapti Nek]], a song being performed by the [[Max Rebo Band/Legends|Max Rebo Band]].<ref name="Return of the Ewok">''[[Return of the Ewok]]''</ref>

